0:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4622:\"\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Feature Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This latest version of Virtual Events includes support for Events Calendar Pro&#8217;s new Summary View.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend making a backup of your site before updating, or updating on a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\">staging site</a>, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-new\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> New</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-new-features-included-in-this-release\">New features included in this release:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Added virtual and hybrid event support into the new Summary View for Events Calendar Pro.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-bugs-that-were-squashed-in-this-release\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Events now correctly show when the event starts when using real object caching.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-developers\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Developers</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-filters-added\"><strong>Filters Added:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_should_show_control_markers</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_assets_should_enqueue_widget_styles</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_assets_should_enqueue_widget_groups</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_encryption_key</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_meetings_zoom_hosts</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_meetings_zoom_alternative_hosts</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_meetings_zoom_user_cache</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_virtual_should_show_control_markers</code></li><li><code>tribe_hybrid_label</code>, <code>tribe_hybrid_event_label_singular</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-actions-added\"><strong>Actions Added:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code><code>tribe_log</code></code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-views-changed\"><strong>Views Changed:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code><code>components/hybrid-event</code></code></li><li><code><code>components/icons/hybrid</code></code></li><li><code><code>components/virtual-event</code></code></li><li><code><code>single/hybrid-marker-mobile</code></code></li><li><code><code>single/hybrid-marker</code></code></li><li><code><code>single/virtual-marker-mobile</code></code></li><li><code><code>single/virtual-marker</code></code></li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-updated-language-files-and-strings\"><strong>Updated language files and strings:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>0 strings added</li><li>2 Strings updated</li><li>0 strings fuzzied</li><li>0 strings obsoleted</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\"></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/virtual-events/virtual-events-1-4-1/\">Virtual Events 1.4.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"Events Calendar Pro 5.7.0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/events-calendar-pro-5-7-0/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 27 May 2021 18:41:30 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2278454\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:594:\"<p>Summary Feature Release This updated version of Events Calendar Pro introduces the new Summary View and several bug fixes. As always, we recommend updating on a staging site, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing. And please note that this is a feature release that focuses on bug fixes and compatibility&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/events-calendar-pro-5-7-0/\">Events Calendar Pro 5.7.0</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"James Welbes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6235:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Feature Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This updated version of Events Calendar Pro introduces the new Summary View and several bug fixes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend updating on a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\">staging site</a>, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing. And please note that this is a feature release that focuses on bug fixes and compatibility with our new <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/the-events-calendar-pro-5-6-0/\">Events Calendar Pro 5.6</a> update.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-new\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> New</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-new-features-included-in-this-release\">New features included in this release:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Introduced the new Summary View!</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-bugs-that-were-squashed-in-this-release\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>When making a Daily, Weekly, Monthly, or Yearly rule, the line for choosing cadence is no longer missing the rule type, e.g. &#8220;Every 6 <strong>days</strong>&#8220;.</li><li>The recurring icon on Map View tooltips now shows.</li><li>Output JavaScript variables are required for events pages when JavaScript is minified.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f527.png\" alt=\"🔧\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-a-few-tweaks-we-made-under-the-hood\">A few tweaks we made under the hood:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Changed the steps used to detect if Yoast Premium was active.</li><li>Updated helper text for the Events Per Page setting in the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/native-elementor-widgets-for-events-calendar-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events View Elementor widget</a>.</li><li>Added Elementor Event Widget support for rendering the hybrid and virtual event indicators from the Virtual Events add-on.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-developers\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Developers</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-filters-added\"><strong>Filters Added:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>tribe_events_pro_editor_recurrence_saver_queue_max_tries</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_pro_elementor_registered_{$this-&gt;type}</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_meta_copier_copy_meta_value</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_meta_copier_block_list</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_pro_shortcodes_countdown_widget_class</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_pro_shortcodes_venue_widget_class</code></li><li><code>tribe_customizer_should_print_shortcode_customizer_styles</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_summary_second_date_in_range</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_week_events_per_day</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_pro_views_v2_widgets_compatibility_id_migration_map</code></li><li><code>tribe_widget_hide_subsequent_recurring_events</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_widget_featured_venue_default_venue_id</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_pro_events_by_week_widget_hide_weekends</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_pro_events_by_week_widget_title_date_format</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-filters-removed\"><strong>Filters Removed:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Deprecated <code>tribe_events_meta_copier_blacklist</code> for <code>tribe_events_meta_copier_block_list</code> (blue_review 2 questions: are these filters? Also, were both whitelist/blacklist replaced with the same thing?)</li><li>Deprecated <code>tribe_events_meta_copier_whitelist</code> for <code>tribe_events_meta_copier_block_list</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-actions-added\"><strong>Actions Added:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>tribe_events_pro_shortcode_month_widget_add_hooks</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_pro_shortcode_month_widget_remove_hooks</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-updated-language-files-and-strings\"><strong>Updated language files and strings:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>9 new strings</li><li>73 strings updated</li><li>0 strings fuzzied</li><li>1 string obsoleted</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/events-calendar-pro-5-7-0/\">Events Calendar Pro 5.7.0</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Filter Bar 5.1.2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/filter-bar/filter-bar-5-1-2/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 27 May 2021 18:41:29 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Filter Bar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2278461\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:574:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release This is a maintenance release that focuses on small tweaks and bug fixes. As always, we recommend updating on a staging site, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixed Bugs squashed in this release: Fixed button styles with the WordPress default theme, Twenty Twenty One. 🔧&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/filter-bar/filter-bar-5-1-2/\">Filter Bar 5.1.2</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"James Welbes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3379:\"\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This is a maintenance release that focuses on small tweaks and bug fixes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend updating on a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\">staging site</a>, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-bugs-squashed-in-this-release\">Bugs squashed in this release:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Fixed button styles with the WordPress default theme, Twenty Twenty One.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f527.png\" alt=\"🔧\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-tweaks-we-made-under-the-hood\"><strong>Tweaks we made under the hood:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Adjusted logic to make sure the correct breakpoint is applied to the calendar.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-developers\"><i class=\"fas fa-code\"></i> Developers</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-new-filters\"><strong>New Filters:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>tribe_events_filter_bar_views_v2_assets_should_enqueue_frontend</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-removed-filters\"><strong>Removed Filters:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>tribe_events_pro_views_v2_assets_should_enqueue_frontend</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-changed-views\"><strong>Changed Views:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>v2_1/filter-bar/breakpoints</code></li><li><code>v2_1/filter-bar/filters-slider</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-updated-language-files-and-strings\"><strong>Updated language files and strings:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>0 strings added</li><li>1 string updated</li><li>0 strings fuzzied</li><li>0 strings obsoleted</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/filter-bar/filter-bar-5-1-2/\">Filter Bar 5.1.2</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"The Events Calendar 5.7.0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-5-7-0/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 27 May 2021 18:41:28 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2278447\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:590:\"<p>Summary Feature Release This updated version of The Events Calendar adds a new Month View section to the WordPress Customizer and includes several bug fixes. As always, we recommend updating on a staging site, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing. And please note that this is a feature release that&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-5-7-0/\">The Events Calendar 5.7.0</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"James Welbes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8289:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Feature Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This updated version of The Events Calendar adds a new Month View section to the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/wordpress-customizer-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WordPress Customizer</a> and includes several bug fixes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend updating on a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\">staging site</a>, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing. And please note that this is a feature release that focuses on bug fixes and compatibility with our new <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/the-events-calendar-pro-5-6-0/\">Events Calendar Pro 5.7</a> update.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-new\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> New</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-new-features-included-in-this-release\">New features included in this release:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Added new Month View section to the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/wordpress-customizer-2/\">WordPress Customizer</a> for users who are using <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/enabling-updated-calendar-views/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">updated calendar views</a>.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-bugs-that-were-squashed-in-this-release\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Applied responsive breakpoints once the page has fully loaded with all JavaScript and elements on the page.</li><li>Resolved conflicts with Gravity Forms plugin that prevented correct submission of forms data.</li><li>Fixed handling of the start and end of day cutoff in Day View when the server timezone is not the same as the site (thanks @therealgilles).</li><li>The <code>archive</code> body class is no longer removed from post tag and category pages when using Default Page Template as event template.</li><li>Fixed translation of calendar view in WPML language switcher (thanks @dgwatkins).</li><li>Fixed &lt;button&gt; styles when using the Twenty Twenty One theme.</li><li>Single event iCalendar export now correctly exports only that event information.</li><li>When Timezone Mode is set to &#8220;Manual time zones for each event&#8221;,  the correct date and time in the Day View time separator are now used</li><li>Fixed conflict with the &#8220;Hello Elementor&#8221; theme to avoid issues with The Events Calendar and Events Calendar PRO views.</li><li>Corrected typo in style output from Customizer. Thanks @apmatthews for catching and correcting this!</li><li>Resolved PHP warnings when linked post types are filtered out (thanks @baden03).</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f527.png\" alt=\"🔧\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-a-few-tweaks-we-made-under-the-hood\">A few tweaks we made under the hood:</h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Removed the usage of the phrase &#8220;Now onwards&#8221; on list-style view date range headings, in favor of the simpler &#8220;Upcoming&#8221;.</li><li>Events from latest past events now display the featured image.</li><li>Moved messages below the calendar grid in the mobile version of Month View.</li><li>Message now displays that lets visitors know the selected Month View day has no events in mobile view.</li><li>Added compatibility for the Full Site Editor navigation block.</li><li>When using Event Aggregator, now only the type of files allowed will be displayed.</li><li>Updated the lodash library to include a security fix.</li><li><em>Skip to Content</em> tab no longer breaks widget icon styles.</li><li>Updated Google Calendar link to use the timezone based on the Timezone Settings from the Calendar.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-developers\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Developers</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-filters-added\"><strong>Filters Added:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Added the <code>tribe_views_v2_after_setup_loop</code> filter to modify the loop context set up in the View (v2).</li><li>Added the <code>tribe_events_views_v2_by_day_view_grid_days</code> to allow pre-filling Month and Week Views (v2) Events.</li><li>Added the <code>tribe_events_views_v2_by_day_view_day_results</code> to allow fine-grained control over Month and Week Views (v2) Event data.</li><li><code>tribe_customizer_should_print_shortcode_customizer_styles</code></li><li><code>tribe_customizer_should_print_shortcode_customizer_styles</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_view_ical_repository_args</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_view_{$slug}_asset_origin_object</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_by_day_view_grid_days</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_by_day_view_day_results</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_month_mobile_messages</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_view_cached_html</code></li><li><code>tribe_events_views_v2_view_{$this->slug}_cached_html</code></li><li><code>tribe_ical_template_event_ids</code>, <code>tribe_get_view_permalink</code></li><li><code>tribe_get_{$slug}_view_permalink</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-actions-added\"><strong>Actions Added:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>tribe_views_v2_after_setup_loop</code></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"h-views-changed\"><strong>Views Changed:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code><code>blocks/classic-event-details</code></code></li><li><code><code>blocks/parts/details</code></code></li><li><code><code>modules/meta/details</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/components/breakpoints</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/components/messages</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/day/time-separator</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/month</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/month/calendar-body/day</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/month/mobile-events</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/month/mobile-events/mobile-day</code></code></li><li><code><code>v2/month/mobile-events/mobile-day/day-marker</code></code></li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<h5 id=\"h-updated-language-files-and-strings\"><strong>Updated language files and strings:</strong></h5>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>27 new strings added</li><li>133 updated</li><li>0 fuzzied</li><li>0 obsoleted</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-5-7-0/\">The Events Calendar 5.7.0</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"How to Add Event Ticket Sales to a WordPress Site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-add-event-ticket-sales-to-a-wordpress-site/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 26 May 2021 14:35:36 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Tips & Tricks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2278068\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:600:\"<p>You’ve planned a great event and you have your guest list ready to go. Now, how do you go about selling tickets so guests can register? By adding tickets to your WordPress site, you can earn ticket revenue and keep track of your attendees in one place. On WordPress, the easiest way to start selling&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-add-event-ticket-sales-to-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Add Event Ticket Sales to a WordPress Site</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Jaime Marchwinski\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7110:\"\n<p>You’ve planned a great event and you have your guest list ready to go. Now, how do you go about selling tickets so guests can register? By <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-sell-event-tickets-on-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">adding tickets</a> to your WordPress site, you can earn ticket revenue and keep track of your attendees in one place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On WordPress, the easiest way to start selling tickets is with the free<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> Event Tickets</a> plugin. Alternatively, you could use a third-party site like Eventbrite to sell tickets. But keeping tickets on your WordPress site with Event Tickets prevents users from navigating away from your site.&nbsp; It also gives you the ability to track ticket sales right from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, adding tickets to your own site can help you earn more money. With Event Tickets, you don’t have to worry about fees associated with third-party sites, which means you can recuperate your overhead costs more quickly.&nbsp;&nbsp;And with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/free-tools-to-help-you-sell-more-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">free tools</a> to help you sell more tickets, there are lots of ways to get the word out and boost sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read on to learn how to start selling tickets on WordPress in a few steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-install-the-event-tickets-plugin\"><strong>Install the Event Tickets plugin</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets</a>, you can add tickets to any WordPress page or post. You can find Event Tickets by searching for it in your WordPress Dashboard under Plugins &gt; Add Plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have installed and activated Event Tickets, you can create a ticket for any custom post type.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> If you’d like <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/do-i-need-event-tickets-or-event-tickets-plus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">additional features</a>, like integration with WooCommerce, custom registration forms, and advanced widgets, you’ll want to upgrade to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-get-familiar-with-the-ticket-settings\"><strong>Get familiar with the ticket settings</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Head over to Events Settings &gt; Tickets to add tickets to all your post types of choice by checking the boxes for each one.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/9PFHhG_PqtaDhaZxP9p6w-pHMWZzvV1D7u87didQv_uIKNfTQIrk8OPLkC3B3wZiurrtw7HNan7qafiS90SRoPuY-4tjS4bO7pKY2TpL66u5KGZ5Rv3AvFZgwPcGuPBJcWw7CJFc\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also make<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/settings-overview-event-tickets-and-event-tickets-plus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> other changes</a> here, like designating where to display tickets on the page and whether users need to be logged in to buy tickets.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are using Event Tickets, your payment gateway will be Tribe Commerce. If you upgrade to Event Tickets Plus, you can choose from other popular payment gateways like WooCommerce or Easy Digital Downloads. You’ll want to consider which ecommerce platform and plugin best meets your needs before you start selling tickets.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click Save when you’re done. Now you can create your first tickets!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-creating-tickets\"><strong>Creating tickets</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Similar to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/how-to-add-an-rsvp-to-a-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">creating an RSVP</a>, adding a ticket to your site is super simple. Head to the WordPress post type where you’d like to add your ticket. Using the Block Editor, you can search for the ticket block and add it to your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pro tip: </strong>If you are adding a ticket to an event post type with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Events Calendar and Events Calendar Pro</a>, this block will display on that page by default.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/vLn-UCcoTeEzRWiXf85CjFBbhaW-laM3P2kHSNLQaCI1Tb_L38DQGBTQFkuauOPPfbukrpM7DOSmRFSdjT2XTqblZSgk7kTHmaWo9qtM_MqKrA0yz8uYGOW27g-Aroo1K0dFCdCl\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, there are options to add a ticket title and price, along with a <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/making-tickets/#global-stock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ticket capacity </a>option that allows you to share the number of remaining tickets, if you’d like. You can also select a Sale Duration and can add <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/collecting-attendee-information/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">attendee information</a> to collect.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure you click <strong>Create Ticket</strong> first and then <strong>Publish</strong> the page or post. Then it’ll look something like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/PcaGhJhUrCKYN9-bCQTrktgYyVhybZsLoSNhaCpYmAN6Iaeqhln-QrliOU1G_1zoDcAMXakd97VrZBipSZ_KPFAyP6OANTz44ukH3pYro4SnwhRAN5Kj53o0BwApH5cNnjTnih4w\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can revisit that ticket on the backend from the <strong>Attendees</strong> tab where you can track sales and see who’s coming to your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-explore-even-more-ticket-features\"><strong>Explore even more ticket features</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that your first tickets are all set up, you can use<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/introducing-new-shortcodes-for-event-tickets-plus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> shortcodes</a> to place ticket information anywhere on your website or<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/customizing-the-ticket-email/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> customize the email template</a> that attendees receive. We have plenty of ticket<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/extensions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> extensions</a> to help you make all your ticketing dreams come true.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-check-out-this-video-for-a-complete-walkthrough\">Check out this video for a complete walkthrough</h2>\n\n\n\n<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/549001855?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-add-event-ticket-sales-to-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Add Event Ticket Sales to a WordPress Site</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"How to Collect Donations with The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-collect-donations-with-the-events-calendar/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 24 May 2021 19:54:25 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Tips & Tricks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2278060\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:641:\"<p>Raising money for a good cause isn’t always easy. But with a few tweaks to your website’s events calendar, there are several ways to showcase your fundraising efforts and bring in more financial support.&#160; Events and donations work in tandem in a variety of scenarios. For example, a musician can collect donations on their livestream&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-collect-donations-with-the-events-calendar/\">How to Collect Donations with The Events Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Jaime Marchwinski\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6013:\"\n<p>Raising money for a good cause isn’t always easy. But with a few tweaks to your website’s events calendar, there are several ways to showcase your fundraising efforts and bring in more financial support.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Events and donations work in tandem in a variety of scenarios. For example, a musician can collect donations on their livestream page where viewers can watch and donate all in one place. Schools can set up fundraising event pages that provide event and donation information all at the same time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you how to make that happen with just a few clicks so you can get back to doing good in the world.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-free-tools-add-convenience-for-you-and-for-donors\"><strong>Free tools add convenience for you and for donors</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Keeping your donations on your WordPress site is key. This allows your users to stay engaged with your event without navigating elsewhere to make donations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll assume you’re already using <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a> to manage your events on WordPress. To get started accepting donations, you&#8217;ll also need to download and install the free <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/give/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GiveWP</a> plugin. This tool allows you to accept charitable gifts through customizable donation forms, view donation statistics and reports, manage donors, and integrate with a variety of third-party gateways and services. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With <a href=\"https://givewp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GiveWP</a> for donations, you can also display your event info on the same page as your donation. This is a great way to maintain a smooth user experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Aside from GiveWP, you do have a few other options to collect donations, like third-party applications that use a PayPal button or redirect users off your site to make a contribution. But most third-party apps take fees out for donations. By using The Events Calendar and GiveWP together, you can avoid third-party fees and be confident that all the money you raise goes toward your cause.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-add-a-donation-form-to-your-events\"><strong>Add a donation form to your events</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Events Calendar</a> and GiveWP on your site, you can use GiveWP to display donation forms and help you view and manage contributions with a few simple steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"647\" height=\"378\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2278061\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM.png 647w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-300x175.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-140x82.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-430x251.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-645x377.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-460x269.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-512x299.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-600x351.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-05-21-at-12.43.10-PM-500x292.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 647px) 100vw, 647px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can activate the Block Editor for your events by going to Events Settings &gt; General and check off “Activate Block Editor.” From there, head to your event and search for the GiveWP block options. Click on the donation form and you automatically have a form ready to accept donations.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/JbfunZ9sKwRQHRHX3dvII21z1OsbAKrjH_NsUlu1JLHbo3BlFbx_BQT_xc632Q2ymWna9oY4RtoCy0KY2SaNQKhinP7O6vjUgP7eBuBMHd4J077xHLxsNimZ3xlrASbIuQ2DEMQx\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn more about how to set up this integration on our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/givewp--the-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Knowledgebase</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-adding-tickets\"><strong>Adding tickets</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re hosting a ticketed event, you can also add tickets to your event with the free <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets</a> plugin. Sponsors can donate to an event, purchase a ticket, and have their contribution displayed on a Donor Wall.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To make this happen, you can use the Donor Wall block within the Block Editor to add a donation option to your ticket page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/t-BtWqbS7ULKJutJ_fh_GowsqLLhFNHZtmba5mJrARbGwLIvj0gLm4p59VCYKr_QBxHXNSq50dHjh15wP62sqZN650QmD5CXVxS5IwKgAgde_Fc3hCp8TUJMfug-oPNrfzivk5hE\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-supercharge-your-events-with-donations\"><strong>Supercharge your events with donations</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating events alongside donations is simple and clean. It’s the best way to keep your donors engaged and excited about contributing to a great cause. And with GiveWP and The Events Calendar, it’s easier than ever to coordinate it all right from your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-collect-donations-with-the-events-calendar/\">How to Collect Donations with The Events Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"How to Add an RSVP to a WordPress Site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/how-to-add-an-rsvp-to-a-wordpress-site/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 19 May 2021 17:45:41 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2276593\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:593:\"<p>You’ve created an awesome event and you can’t wait for everyone to come. But you have guests responding via email, phone, and text, and it’s hard to keep it all straight! By adding an RSVP to your WordPress site, you can streamline the process so that you have one less thing to worry about. Adding&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/how-to-add-an-rsvp-to-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Add an RSVP to a WordPress Site</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Jaime Marchwinski\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5219:\"\n<p>You’ve created an awesome event and you can’t wait for everyone to come. But you have guests responding via email, phone, and text, and it’s hard to keep it all straight! By adding an RSVP to your WordPress site, you can streamline the process so that you have one less thing to worry about.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding this feature to your site will keep you more organized in the long run. It will also help you save time so you can focus on preparing for the event and making sure all goes according to plan.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/why-you-should-add-rsvp-to-your-free-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Adding an RSVP to a WordPress site</a> is super simple, and you don’t need to write a single line of code to make it happen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below, we’ll walk through how to do it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-installing-event-tickets\"><strong>Installing Event Tickets</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With the free <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets</a> plugin, you can create RSVP forms and manage your registrations right from WordPress. You can find Event Tickets by searching for it in your WordPress Dashboard under Plugins &gt; Add Plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have installed and activated <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets</a>, you can add an RSVP to any custom post type.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> You can also add RSVPs to a calendar of events by using Event Tickets with our free <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Events Calendar</a> plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-explore-the-settings\"><strong>Explore the settings</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll want to head over to Events Settings &gt; Tickets and make sure that you check off whatever post type you’d like to use. Even though it says “tickets,” these settings also apply to your RSVP.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/K8obsFOKii_nDjE0DVyats1u5BYGIQzH-XaHkqZuN96PhNd0tlVEPPBDiFxJGa8xNtTzgqtSJS7W1LtaZDGrA42GwimK7WHn0Gd2WNvu_9Rhr1AybbgEVVs3PRLPGCJkX_zez5yW\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also make changes here about the location of the RSVP form and decide whether you’d like users to log in before creating an RSVP.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-creating-the-rsvp\"><strong>Creating the RSVP</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve adjusted your settings, you can begin creating the RSVP form. To do this, head over to the custom post type where you’d like the RSVP to appear.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can search for the RSVP block with the Gutenberg Editor. Once you find it, an RSVP form will be added to your post type of choice.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><img width=\"624\" height=\"443\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/u1cdPVZ9DAXMFsNF1gFqRoK6-L-MEBJzrFugRIup2Yev0o8gl3VZlAY_pVh_qMe47mc9Zqq2dXCU0E8T5lAycQl1fdd5V2SM2CsOMr4rtsl4_7KcafZ4jchzKyH9EuOig-JLfoWj\"></p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add a capacity limit and allow the option to let users choose “Going” or “Not Going” instead of only enabling RSVP if they plan to attend. You can also set how long to display this RSVP.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you expand the Settings on your RSVP, you can add a Header Image to the RSVP. Once you click Create RSVP, your finished product will look something like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/u3q6EcNy0hwUomvqZTUwxU-Z5u21XjsasEx29p0eHHusbuf6BaZdEB8rknEgd0CyO1wr3qfrsDinySFmahCkRqzEXqYPmodrop0NZ_BlAzxDCYyNY9Dk9XXR8-52BiIJp_ETM3_R\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-keeping-track-of-it-all\"><strong>Keeping track of it all</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that people have started to RSVP, you can keep track of who’s coming on the Attendees screen. You can get to this page by locating your RSVP then clicking on Attendees in the top toolbar. You can also find it by clicking on the RSVP itself, which now has an Attendees option added.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/MqhkRO2mnsAkQQ1Uw2lDXOGLJxcgR7b89s5jQN8IQBzqhMpoX56hBB_TrjepNYFkGebcMYL1yAOyAQG2E7xFHF8m3PoBuZ_qRoYI0Vw21WzFGhYmltrWgKaN59hVo8rg1oQiOaYK\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-upgrade-for-more-ticketing-and-rsvp-options\"><strong>Upgrade for more ticketing and RSVP options</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Want even more features? By upgrading to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a>, you can connect to WooCommerce, add <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/collecting-attendee-information/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">custom fields</a> to your registration forms, and check your attendees in with a QR code. These extra features can save you time and help you to customize your user experience.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/how-to-add-an-rsvp-to-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Add an RSVP to a WordPress Site</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"How to Customize Your Calendar and Events with Kadence WP\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/how-to-customize-your-calendar-and-events-with-kadence-wp/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 12 May 2021 18:01:46 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Tips & Tricks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"What\'s New\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2266707\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:671:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited that Kadence WP has joined StellarWP, a new umbrella brand for all of Liquid Web&#8217;s software offerings! Kadence WP is the maker of the popular Kadence Theme and a powerful collection of blocks for effortlessly creating gorgeous webpages. Kadence Theme and Kadence Blocks work great with The Events Calendar, and we wanted to share&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/how-to-customize-your-calendar-and-events-with-kadence-wp/\">How to Customize Your Calendar and Events with Kadence WP</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Geoff\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38789:\"\n<p><p>We&#8217;re excited that Kadence WP has joined <a href=\"https://stellarwp.com/\">StellarWP</a>, a new umbrella brand for all of Liquid Web&#8217;s software offerings! </p></p>\n\n\n\n<p><p>Kadence WP is the maker of the popular <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/kadence/\">Kadence Theme</a> and <a href=\"https://www.kadenceblocks.com\">a powerful collection of blocks</a> for effortlessly creating gorgeous webpages.</p></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-background\" href=\"https://www.kadencewp.com/?utm_campaign=xsell&amp;utm_source=tec&amp;utm_medium=blog\" style=\"background-color:#3d54ff\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Learn More About Kadence</a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>Kadence Theme and Kadence Blocks work great with The Events Calendar, and we wanted to share a few helpful tips for using these tools in harmony to make your events really stand out.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-initial-setup\">Initial setup</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Kadence is <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/kadence/\">available to download for free</a>, or you can install it directly in WordPress on the Appearance → Themes → Add New screen.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2386\" height=\"2128\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266747\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence.png 2386w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-300x268.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-665x593.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-95x85.png 95w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-768x685.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-1536x1370.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-2048x1827.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-430x384.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-645x575.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-2000x1784.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-1068x953.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-460x410.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-1602x1429.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-1074x958.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-512x457.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-1611x1437.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-1236x1102.png 1236w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-594x530.png 594w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-1853x1653.png 1853w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-600x535.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-appearance-themes-add-kadence-500x446.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2386px) 100vw, 2386px\" /><figcaption>Search for &#8220;Kadence&#8221; in the WordPress admin.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t already installed The Events Calendar, it&#8217;s time to install that next. Like Kadence, the plugin is <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\">free to download</a> or install in the WordPress admin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, we need to make the calendar the homepage of the site. To do this, hop over to Reading Settings screen (Settings → General → Reading) and select the main events page as the site&#8217;s front page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2340\" height=\"1886\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266750\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage.png 2340w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-300x242.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-665x536.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-105x85.png 105w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-768x619.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-1536x1238.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-2048x1651.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-430x347.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-645x520.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-2000x1612.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-1068x861.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-460x371.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-1602x1291.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-1074x866.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-512x413.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-1611x1298.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-1367x1102.png 1367w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-658x530.png 658w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-600x484.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-settings-reading-homepage-500x403.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2340px) 100vw, 2340px\" /><figcaption>The &#8220;Main Events Page&#8221; is automatically created when The Events Calendar is activated.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s it for the initial setup! If we were to stop here and do nothing else, we can already see how great the calendar and Kadence look together out of the box on the homepage.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2982\" height=\"2988\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266758\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view.png 2982w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-300x301.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-665x666.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-85x85.png 85w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-768x770.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-1533x1536.png 1533w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-2044x2048.png 2044w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-430x431.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-645x646.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-2000x2004.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-180x180.png 180w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-270x270.png 270w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-1068x1070.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-460x461.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-1602x1605.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-1074x1076.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-512x513.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-1611x1614.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-1100x1102.png 1100w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-529x530.png 529w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-1650x1653.png 1650w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-150x150.png 150w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-100x100.png 100w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-600x601.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-tec-month-view-500x501.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2982px) 100vw, 2982px\" /><figcaption><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f60d.png\" alt=\"😍\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Lovely, right?</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a lovely, clean calendar, but there are so many more ways you can use the Kadence Theme to make the calendar and your events stand out.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-customized-page-styling\">Customized page styling</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><p>Kadence&#8217;s flexibility shines when it comes to customizing the style of a page. Simply open up the WordPress Customizer (Appearance → Customize) to see all of the options that are available.</p>\n<p>Kadence extends the normal Customizer options with everything from layouts and fonts to colors and spacing, with granular control so you can tweak just about everything on the page.</p></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"3294\" height=\"2456\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266766\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout.png 3294w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-300x224.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-665x496.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-114x85.png 114w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-768x573.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-1536x1145.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-2048x1527.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-260x195.png 260w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-430x321.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-645x481.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-2000x1491.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-1068x796.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-460x343.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-1602x1194.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-1074x801.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-512x382.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-1611x1201.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-1478x1102.png 1478w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-707x527.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-600x447.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-customizer-kadence-page-layout-500x373.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 3294px) 100vw, 3294px\" /><figcaption>All of these settings are just for styling the page title!</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s the catch: <strong>These settings don&#8217;t work automatically with the default event page</strong>. That&#8217;s because the calendar is not actually a page, but an archive. To work around this, let&#8217;s open up the &#8220;Blog Posts&#8221; settings, where there&#8217;s an option to customize the archive appearance.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-using-starter-templates\">Using starter templates</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With Kadence WP, you can install <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/kadence-starter-templates/\">starter templates</a> as a separate plugin. The benefit of a template is that it provides the layout for you. Simply swap the placeholder content with your own and you&#8217;ve got a great webpage in a matter of minutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s go ahead and put those free starter templates to work. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/kadence-starter-templates/\">Install the template plugin</a>, activate it, then choose a template for the calendar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"3118\" height=\"2676\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266775\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates.png 3118w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-300x257.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-665x571.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-99x85.png 99w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-768x659.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-1536x1318.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-2048x1758.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-430x369.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-645x554.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-2000x1716.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-1068x917.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-460x395.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-1602x1375.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-1074x922.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-512x439.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-1611x1383.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-1284x1102.png 1284w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-618x530.png 618w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-1926x1653.png 1926w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-600x515.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-admin-kadence-starter-templates-500x429.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 3118px) 100vw, 3118px\" /><figcaption>Kadence&#8217;s pack of starter templates offers several pre-made layouts that make designing a page a cinch.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After selecting a template, Kadence will import it to the site complete with dummy content and images that you can replace with your own. It even lets you choose a preconfigured color theme that can be applied to either to the page or the entire site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We chose the &#8220;SaaS&#8221; template for this example. It has a modern design that looks like it would work well for a venue that hosts live music.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"665\" height=\"459\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-665x459.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266785\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-665x459.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-300x207.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-123x85.png 123w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-768x530.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-1536x1060.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-2048x1413.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-430x297.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-645x445.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-2000x1380.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-1068x737.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-460x317.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-1602x1105.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-1074x741.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-512x353.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-1611x1111.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-1597x1102.png 1597w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-707x488.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-600x414.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-4.55.39-PM-500x345.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /><figcaption>Here&#8217;s what we&#8217;re working with.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The trick here is to add <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\">Events Calendar Pro</a> to the mix. It allows the full calendar to be <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/guide/shortcodes/#events-calendar-pro\">embedded on any page with a shortcode</a>. And, because the WordPress block editor has a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/shortcode-block/\">block specifically for shortcodes</a>, embedding the calendar on the page is easy. Insert the block, enter <code>[tribe_events]</code> into it, and the full calendar displays on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2678\" height=\"2220\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266787\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM.png 2678w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-300x249.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-665x551.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-103x85.png 103w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-768x637.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-1536x1273.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-2048x1698.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-430x356.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-645x535.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-2000x1658.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-1068x885.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-460x381.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-1602x1328.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-1074x890.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-512x424.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-1611x1335.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-1329x1102.png 1329w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-639x530.png 639w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-1994x1653.png 1994w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-600x497.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/Screen-Shot-2021-04-13-at-5.09.20-PM-500x414.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2678px) 100vw, 2678px\" /><figcaption>The Shortcode Block support the calendar shortcodes offered in Events Calendar Pro.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With a few tweaks here and there using Kadence&#8217;s wide variety of settings, we can make a slick calendar page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2418\" height=\"5132\" src=\"https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2266795\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar.png 2418w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-141x300.png 141w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-482x1024.png 482w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-40x85.png 40w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-768x1630.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-724x1536.png 724w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-965x2048.png 965w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-430x913.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-645x1369.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-2000x4245.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-1068x2267.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-460x976.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-1602x3400.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-1074x2279.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-512x1087.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-1611x3419.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-519x1102.png 519w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-250x530.png 250w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-779x1653.png 779w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-300x637.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-377x800.png 377w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/wp-kadence-tec-calendar-500x1061.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2418px) 100vw, 2418px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-creating-event-pages-with-kadence-blocks\">Creating event pages with Kadence Blocks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, there&#8217;s blocks. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/kadence-blocks/\">Kadence Blocks</a> is a massive (and free!) collection of elements that can be dropped into the block editor and arranged to create layouts. Even better, <a href=\"https://www.kadenceblocks.com/prebuilt-library/\">Kadence Blocks include a bunch of pre-built designs</a> that make creating pages fast and easy. You can think of them as <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress/how-to-work-with-wordpress-block-patterns/\">block patterns:</a> They&#8217;re reusable groups of blocks that form layout components.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2226\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://ik.imagekit.io/wddsiy1na/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1.png\" alt=\"Three tiles in a row, each with a screenshot of different Kadence block patterns: header (left), three card panel (center), and a two-button call to action (right).\" class=\"wp-image-2267042\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1.png 2226w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-300x61.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-665x134.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-140x28.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-768x155.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-1536x311.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-2048x414.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-430x87.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-645x130.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-2000x404.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-1068x216.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-460x93.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-1602x324.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-1074x217.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-512x104.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-1611x326.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-707x143.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-600x121.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-blocks-patterns-1-500x101.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2226px) 100vw, 2226px\" /><figcaption>Just a few of the many block patterns included in Kadence Blocks.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Kadence Blocks are the <em>perfect</em> tool for making beautiful and engaging event pages. They work with events, giving you full control to make the page look however you want!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2060\" height=\"3478\" src=\"https://ik.imagekit.io/wddsiy1na/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2267066\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout.png 2060w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-178x300.png 178w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-607x1024.png 607w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-50x85.png 50w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-768x1297.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-910x1536.png 910w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-1213x2048.png 1213w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-430x726.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-645x1089.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-2000x3377.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-1068x1803.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-460x777.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-1602x2705.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/04/kadence-event-layout-1074x1813.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2021/