Event Tickets Plus\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2274586\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:619:\"<p>&#160; Summary Maintenance Release Event Tickets Plus 5.2.4 adds several improvements to the general usability and user experience of the plugin, as well as improvements to its stability. This is a &#8220;maintenance&#8221; release, meaning it should be a super smooth update but, as always, please back up your site and database as you would with&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-5-2-4/\">Event Tickets Plus 5.2.4</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Leopoldo Scanavino\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2869:\"\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">Event Tickets Plus 5.2.4 adds several improvements to the general usability  and user experience of the plugin, as well as improvements to its stability.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a &#8220;maintenance&#8221; release, meaning it should be a super smooth update but, as always, please back up your site and database as you would with any other WordPress update.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The following items were fixed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Who’s Attending</strong> count should now account for purchasers that have opted out of the public list.</li><li>On the Attendee Registration modal, the <em>Remove</em> functionality (the X on the left side of a Ticket or RSVP) now re-calculates the amount of tickets and total value of an order.</li><li>Fixed an &#8220;insecure request&#8221; response which didn&#8217;t allow to use the Manual Attendee Add &amp; ARI Edit functionality. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-new\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> New</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">We have included the following new items in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul id=\"block-151c1d59-5948-45c8-a2c7-9d0753786f3e\"><li>When using the Classic Editor, each Ticket or RSVP will now show which Attendee Registration Fields have been included.</li><li>We have included a custom placeholder field for the following Attendee Registration Fields: text, email, telephone and URL.</li><li>You can now use the filter <code>event_tickets_plus_requested_api_is_valid</code> within the QR Code check-in API to allow usage of separate API keys for each Event.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-5-2-4/\">Event Tickets Plus 5.2.4</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Event Tickets 5.1.4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets/event-tickets-5-1-4/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 12 May 2021 17:41:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Event Tickets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40: