erventions for Neurological Conditions</em>\".  The sessions will run in two 1-hour blocks on <strong>Thursday 10<sup>th</sup> September 2015 (Time to be confirmed) </strong>and will be held at the North Sydney campus of ACU.\n\nParticipants will be asked to engage with small groups of students in a practice interview, where students will have a chance to ask you carefully prepared questions about your everyday life  and the changes you have experienced in your life since your stroke.  The information students collect will be used as a basis for an assignment to develop a therapy plan from an initial interview.  Your name will not be used in the assignment to maintain confidentiality. It would be good to hear whether anyone would be willing to lend their time for this activity.\n\nTaxi vouchers for transport will be provided or we can assist with organising parking on campus. We are aware of the positive and influential impact past patients can have on students and feel this experience will be invaluable for them as they prepare to be qualified occupational therapists. I would be happy to provide any other information needed and can be contacted at <a href=\"mailto:Ruth.Swanton@acu.edu.au\">Ruth.Swanton@acu.edu.au</a>','Australian Catholic University North Sydney Campus','','publish','closed','closed','','australian-catholic-university-north-sydney-campus','','','2017-05-17 11:49:11','2017-05-17 11:49:11','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=stroke_research&amp;p=135',0,'stroke_research','',0),(136,1,'2017-05-17 11:50:54','2017-05-17 11:50:54','Content','Publications test','','publish','closed','closed','','publications-test','','','2017-05-17 11:50:54','2017-05-17 11:50:54','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=stroke_publications&amp;p=136',0,'stroke_publications','',0),(157,1,'2017-09-07 05:39:12','2017-09-07 05:39:12','','Contact','','publish','closed','closed','','contact','','','2020-12-01 01:33:03','2020-12-01 01:33:03','',0,'http://localhost/?page_id=157',0,'page',