o develop communication skills. Speech Pathologists also have specific skills to support people who have difficulty with eating, drinking or swallowing their food.\r\nDo you, your child or young person require help to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>join in conversations with all the people in your life like family, friends and teachers?</li>\r\n 	<li>understand what people say and learn the words you need to express ideas and feelings?</li>\r\n 	<li>use pictures, signs or technology like Augmentative and Alternate Communication (AAC) devices to communicate?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nA speech pathologist can help you, your child or young person to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>develop communication skills in the daily interactions, routines and activities you enjoy</li>\r\n 	<li>learn speech sounds, words and sentences to express ideas</li>\r\n 	<li>understand what words mean and how to follow instructions\r\nlearn social skills</li>\r\n 	<li>understand and use gestures, signs and pictures to support communication</li>\r\n 	<li>identify technology that can assist with communication and to use the technology e.g. Augmentative and Alternative Communication (AAC) Systems</li>\r\n 	<li>identify specific difficulties with eating and drinking and assist with feeling safe when swallowing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Do we provide services in your area?</h4>\r\nWe provide supports in the Sydney metropolitan area including - Western Sydney, Northern Sydney, Northern Beaches and parts of South Western Sydney, the Inner West and South Eastern Sydney.\r\n<h4>What is the cost?</h4>\r\nCosts vary depending on the service provided. You can use your NDIS funding package (we offer services under the NDIS support areas of Improved Daily Living and Improved Relationships) or pay privately.\r\n<h4>Contact us</h4>\r\nTo find out more call our Client Engagement Team on<strong> 1800 953 390.</strong>','Speech therapy','','publish','closed','closed','','speech-therapy','','','2018-08-12 23:11:48','2018-08-12 23:11:48','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=services&#038;p=352',0,'services','',0),(353,1,'2018-08-12 23:15:21','2018-08-12 23:15:21','<h4>What do we offer?</h4>\r\nWe support children and young people living with disability to develop the skills to be part of everyday life in their community.\r\nWe provide flexible, person-centred therapy supports for children and young people aged 0-24 years. Our multidisciplinary teams consist of specialist professionals who are experienced in working with children and young people living with disability.\r\n\r\nThey include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>speech pathologists</li>\r\n 	<li>occupational therapists</li>\r\n 	<li>physiotherapists</li>\r\n 	<li>behaviour specialists</li>\r\n 	<li>social workers and psychologists</li>\r\n 	<li>educators.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe work in partnership with families and carers to provide individualised supports that are responsive to the unique abilities, interests and aspirations of children and young people. We will support you, your child or young person in a place of your choosing which could be in your home, preschool, school, or other places that you spend time.\r\n\r\nLifestart may also use a key worker approach depending on the type of support you require. A key worker is the person you and your family and carers will see and talk to most and may be any one of our specialist professionals depending on your needs and goals.\r\n<h4>Do we provide services in your area?</h4>\r\nWe provide therapy supports in the Sydney metropolitan area including - Western Sydney, Northern Sydney, Northern Beaches and parts of South Western Sydney, the Inner West and South Eastern Sydney.\r\n<h4>\r\nWhat is the cost?</h4>\r\nCosts vary depending on the service provided. You can use your NDIS funding package (we offer services under the NDIS support areas of Improved Daily Living and Improved Relationships) or pay privately.\r\n<h4>Contact us</h4>\r\nTo find out more call our Client Engagement Team on 1800 953 390.','Therapy supports','','pu