nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC/ ACP</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vaia Toussas</td>\r\n<td>What are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Peter</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Infection control – ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Will the department ensure the families that residents will not return until permission has been given by family?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC/ DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Nikki Kontos</td>\r\n<td>How often will COVID-19 testing be conducted when residents return?</td>\r\n<td>DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Document the role of the Commission in making sure no one is sent back to St Basil’s unless it’s safe?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n	\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">Bereavement</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Spiros Dimitriou</td>\r\n<td>What support is available to families that have lost loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat support is available to families that have lost loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Mia</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat support is available to families that have lost loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">ACQSC Audit &amp; VIC Coronial Inquiry</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Christine Golding</td>\r\n<td>How is the ACQSC going to conduct an audit when St Basil’s is not open and during lockdown? What is the step-by-step process of the audit?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>John Bahtsevanoglou</td>\r\n<td>During the audit and inquiry:\r\n\r\nWhat are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will 