st loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Mia</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat support is available to families that have lost loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">ACQSC Audit &amp; VIC Coronial Inquiry</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Christine Golding</td>\r\n<td>How is the ACQSC going to conduct an audit when St Basil’s is not open and during lockdown? What is the step-by-step process of the audit?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>John Bahtsevanoglou</td>\r\n<td>During the audit and inquiry:\r\n\r\nWhat are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC/ ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Who will make a representation to the Victorian Coronial inquiry?</td>\r\n<td>DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Does the Victorian Coronial inquiry cover both COVID-19 positive and negative cases?</td>\r\n<td>DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">Protocol</h2>\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Spiros Dimitriou</td>\r\n<td>Did St Basils management report the first COVID case within the required period of time as per \"first 24hr report\" and then follow process as stated in that report.</td>\r\n<td>ACP - DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Ralph</td>\r\n<td>How were residents kept isolated in their rooms once the first case of COVID was reported? Please explain the process that was undertaken</td>\r\n<td>ACP - DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nHow were residents kept isolated in their rooms once the first case of COVID was reported? Please explain the process that was undertaken</td>\r\n<td>ACP DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Did St Basil’s deploy an infection control plan after the first case was known, and what was it?</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Why were St Basil’s Management unable to contain the virus from spreading throughout the nursing home?</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>What training was provided to staff on infection control and correct use of PPE? Please specify dates and type of training conducted</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>DUPLICATE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nWhat training was provided to staff on infection control and correct use of PPE? Please specify dates and type of training conducted</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>What infection control plan was executed at St Basil’s once the first COVID positive case was found?</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>Why were St Basil’s Management unable to contain the virus from spreading throughout the nursing home?</td>\r\n<td> ACP/ACQSC\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>What training was provided to staff on infection control and correct use of PPE? Please specify dates and type of training conducted</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat training was provided to staff on infection control and correct use of PPE? Please specify dates and type of training conducted</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nWhat was the exact date Tony Papantoniou’s mother was isolated in her room?</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nWhat were the exact dates Tony Papantoniou’s mother was tested for COVID-19? Provide copy of results.</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nIf Tony Papantoniou’s mother was isolated in her room how and why was she infected, when she is immobile and cannot leave her room without assistance?</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>Why were families not informed when  the virus spread from high care nursing to other sections?</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ Independent evaluator</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>Please document the step-by-step process that took place when Aspen Medical took over. Families want to know why medical, dietary and care needs were not met</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nWhy was Tony Papantoniou’s mother’s catheter care neglected and needed to be sent to hospital with a serious infection. Three weeks later it is still infected\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>ACP /ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nWhy was Tony Papantoniou’s mother’s dehydrated and malnourished when admitted to      hospital on the 24th July?</td>\r\n<td>ACP /</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nTony Papantoniou is requesting a copy of his mother’s medical and dietary chart from the 01st July to the 24th of July. He needs a date this can be furnished</td>\r\n<td> ACP /ACQSC\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nTony Papantoniou would like to know why his mother’s care was neglected</td>\r\n<td>ACP /ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">Neglect of Care</h2>\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/ Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vaia Toussas</td>\r\n<td>Timeline of events from 22/7/2020 to 26/7/2020 including processes undertook, care provided, infection control measures and protocols followed</td>\r\n<td>DoH/ ACQS</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vaia Toussas</td>\r\n<td>SPECIFIC CASE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nWhat led to Vaia Toussas’s father becoming dehydrated and malnourished with a nasty rash on his chest and severe pressure sores on his sacrum and heel.\r\n\r\nWhy was he not diagnosed as COVID positive at St Basil’s? He was tested at the Peninsula Private hospital on admission and diagnosed with COVID-19 on 29/7/2020.</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vaia Toussas</td>\r\n<td>What led to residents becoming severely dehydrated and malnourished? (as reported by hospital staff, specifically Peninsula Private in one case)</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vaia Toussas</td>\r\n<td>What reassurances can we give families that care issues will be investigated? What is the process we can share with them?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Outline the processes that took place during isolation. Where residents sedated, fed, hydrated, medicated as normal. List isolation practices that were employed</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Outline the processes that took place during isolation. Where residents sedated, fed, hydrated, medicated as normal. List isolation practices that were employed</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Why were residents dehydrated, malnourished and in poor health when transferred to hospital? Families would like to know the timeline of events, processes and care that led to this point</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</t